node.text: Does your new houseplant need a new home? Transplanting them into larger pots will help them grow better, bigger, and stronger. But growth isn’t the only reason to repot: You may have a plant that looks a little sickly and in need of a nutrient boost, which it’ll get when you add new soil to its current container. Watch plant expert Katura Barnes (@terracottahotties) share her tips for repotting houseplants including what containers she loves to use and what combination of soil she prefers for her plant babies. https://bit.ly/3xUw5OC

node.text: Whether you're a fan of peaches, crazy for rhubarb, just adore apricots, or are mad about berries, here's your route to an irresistible fruit crumble that serves eight. Here, our basic peach crumble features a topping of butter, flour, brown sugar, and a touch of salt (and is the same recipe for our variations). Even better, the crumble can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen, so we suggest making a double batch and saving half for future desserts. Once you master our recipe, try different flavor combinations with your favorite summer fruit. Visit the link in bio to learn more! 📷: @conpoulos_photographer

node.text: Watch senior digital editor, @victoriaspencers, use Lillet Rosé, a fortified-wine blend, to make a delicious, citrusy cocktail that’s perfect for serving at your next happy hour. Plus, use edible flowers for a statement-making garnish guests will love. Get the recipe here or at the link in bio: https://bit.ly/3x9RTEv

node.text: We love this sheet cake-like take on creamy cheesecake that will serve a crowd since it's made in three simple steps. Whipped cream folded into this no-bake beauty’s lemony ricotta-and-cream-cheese filling gives it an airy texture and ethereal taste, all of which is sandwiched between a mellow vanilla wafer crust and burst of blueberry. Get the recipe at the link in bio! 📷 @alphamay

node.text: No time in the oven is required to make this light and cheesy lasagna. Our recipe calls for grape tomatoes, zucchini, ricotta, and grated Parmesan. Plus, the lasagna noodles, of course! Get the recipe at the link in bio.

node.text: One of @marthastewartt48’s favorite desserts to make during the summer? Buttermilk ice cream! Watch Martha and culinary director Thomas Joseph (@tojo827) make a simple buttermilk ice cream that’s perfect for pairing with peanut pie. Get the recipe here or at the link in bio: https://bit.ly/2Vk7zI3

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Martha Stewart on July 27, 2021 tagging @brooklyncooks, @linda.xiao, @marthastewart, @sarahcarey1, and @suzie_myers. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: As the tomato vines burst forth with the vibrant and versatile summer fruit, let them land on this plate of chicken-and-eggplant "caprese." This riff on the beloved Italian salad adds grilled chicken breast, grilled eggplant, kalamata olives, and fresh parsley but the tomatoes remain the stars. Get the recipe featured in our July/August issue at the link in bio. 📷: @linda.xiao recipe by: @sarahcarey1 food styling by: @brooklyncooks prop styling by: @suzie_myers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Martha Stewart on July 27, 2021 tagging @marthastewart, and @pissinginthepunchbowl. May be an image of strawberry, dessert and indoor.

node.text: Make this syrupy, ruby red strawberry sauce with just three ingredients—berries, sugar, and lemon juice. From here, mix it into homemade ice cream, serve over Greek yogurt or cottage cheese, or drizzle over slices of pound cake and ice cream for a strawberry-shortcake sundae. Get the recipe at the link in bio! 📷: @pissinginthepunchbowl
